 @G[c3 stills_137.png]@L
		@H Historical Background @L
		The Romans established many colonies named Caesarea across the Mediterranean. This was obviously an homage to the Gaius Julius Caesar. After his death, his name was enshrined and he received a god-like reverence. One could argue that it was the first case where cult of personality would develop. This tradition carried on when Rome became an Empire and even Augustus's name received the same treatment, virtually becoming synonymous with "hegemon". @L@L
		Caesarea in Roman Mauretania was originally the Phoenician city of Iol, later coming under the rule of Carthage and then Numidia after the Punic Wars ended. Following the assassination of Julius Caesar, the city was ruled by King Juba II, a Berber prince whom Caesar had taken prisoner as a child and had educated in Italy as a Roman citizen. @L@L
		Juba II fought alongside Octavian, the future emperor Augustus, and married Cleopatra Selene, daughter of the infamous Marc Anthony and Cleopatra VII of Egypt. Juba and his wife were given rule over Mauretania and renamed their capital Caesarea to honor their benefactor and rebuilt the city using both Roman and Egyptian stylistic features. Greek, Punic, Roman, and Berber cultures lived together in the city in relative harmony during this period. @L@L
		
		@G[c3 instructions icon.png]
		@H Instructions @L
		Governor, take command of the city and build it into a splendid Roman colony. This assignment will present a new type of challenge: there is no viable food source in Caesarea, so to ensure supply for your garrison and prosperity for your city, you will have to rely entirely on imports from the wider Republic. @L@L
		Fortunately, the climate favors cultivation of olives and vines near local oases. Additionally, gold and stone may be extracted from the surrounding mountains, so the export industry promises to be very lucrative. The terrain around the city is not overly rugged, but local raiders will take an interest in the city. @L@L
		You must repel their constant attacks on a regular basis. You should consider investing into substantial patrols all along the outskirts of the city. The more quickly each wave of raiders is defeated, the sooner you can continue expanding your city further. @L@L
		You should start with a prebuilt city in this assignment but since this would force a similar design for every player, it was abandoned to promote more original designs. @L@L
		
		@H Edicts @L@
		Piracy - Local pirates will often attack merchant ships and disrupt trade. Significant military buildup can prevent this via an event later. @L@L
		@Impossible @Self-Sufficiency - Foodstuffs and certain other goods are only available via imports. A future event will offer a way to gain some additional food for free. @L@L
		@H Additional Information @L
		At the time of the mission, Rome was a republic so treat requests from "Caesar" as if they were from the Roman Senate instead.@L
		@H Persistent Events @L@L
		Grand Temple to Mercury unlocks plaza. Subsidies, lasting until 10 prosperity rating, give 100 dn. per month. Workshops only unlock after the subsidy expires. @L@L
		Due to game limitations, starting prices for goods will be adjusted after 1 in-game month has passed. @L@L@L@L

